<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1802" authorityName="Rosa, Proshchalykin &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychridium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychridium erythrosoma" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrosoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Hedychridium erythrosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is recognised by red body colour, with head and thorax coppery red, darker to violet on vertex, pronotum and mesoscutum; greenish on face and at sides of metasomal segments; metasomal sutures black; metasoma red flame dorsally, black ventrally; metanotum distinctly elongate, trapezoidal; metatibial [= hind tibial] spot short, impressed; male with distinct genital capsule.
</paragraph>
